=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Formant_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A neutral pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 709 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, and filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: neutral
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: moderate
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 708.6140
  harmonic_decay_rate: -2.1806
  harmonic_regularity: 0.0685
  pitch_clarity: 50.3670
  inharmonicity: 0.2864
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -20.7721
  resonance_freq: 2045.6543

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Formant Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Formant.html
// Tags: Formant, Classes, oscillator
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
// modulate fundamental frequency, formant freq stays constant
{ Formant.ar(XLine.kr(400, 1000, 8), 2000, 800, 0.125) }.play

// modulate formant frequency, fundamental freq stays constant
{ Formant.ar(200, XLine.kr(400, 4000, 8), 200, 0.125) }.play

// modulate width frequency, other freqs stay constant
{ Formant.ar(400, 2000, XLine.kr(800, 8000, 8), 0.125) }.play
